@startuml

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName "Segoe UI"
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam usecase {
    BackgroundColor #F8F9FA
    BorderColor #495057
    FontColor #212529
}
skinparam actor {
    BackgroundColor #E9ECEF
    BorderColor #6C757D
    FontColor #212529
}
skinparam rectangle {
    BackgroundColor #E9ECEF
    BorderColor #6C757D
    FontColor #212529
}
skinparam note {
    BackgroundColor #FFF9C4
    BorderColor #F9A825
    FontColor #333333
}
skinparam ArrowColor #495057

left to right direction

title WordPress Recovery Mode Workflow\n(Error Protection API — introduced in WordPress 5.2)

actor "Site Admin" as admin
actor "WordPress\nSystem" as wp
actor "Cron\nScheduler" as cron

rectangle "WordPress Recovery Mode" {

    usecase "Detect Fatal Error" as UC1
    usecase "Send Recovery\nMode Email" as UC2
    usecase "Generate Recovery\nURL & One-Time Key" as UC3
    usecase "Enter Recovery Mode\nvia Secure Link" as UC4
    usecase "Validate Recovery\nSession Cookie" as UC5
    usecase "Pause Faulty\nPlugin / Theme" as UC6
    usecase "Exit Recovery Mode" as UC7
    usecase "Clean Expired\nRecovery Keys" as UC8

}

' Actor associations
wp    --> UC1
wp    --> UC2
wp    --> UC5
admin --> UC4
admin --> UC6
admin --> UC7
cron  --> UC8

' Include / Extend relationships
UC2 ..> UC3 : <<include>>
UC2 ..> UC1 : <<extend>>\nwhen: protected endpoint\n& recovery not yet active

' Notes — key business rules
note right of UC1
  <b>WP_Fatal_Error_Handler</b> detects PHP fatal error.
  Identifies source plugin/theme via file path.
  Network-activated plugins are excluded.
  Only plugin/theme errors (not core) trigger
  the recovery workflow.
end note

note right of UC2
  <b>Rate-limited:</b> one email per day
  (filterable: recovery_mode_email_rate_limit).
  Recipient resolved from RECOVERY_MODE_EMAIL
  constant or admin_email site option.
  Returns WP_Error 'email_sent_already' if
  within rate-limit window.
end note

note right of UC3
  <b>One-time use key:</b> token generated via
  wp_generate_password(22); key hashed with
  PasswordHash and stored in DB option 'recovery_keys'.
  Key is deleted immediately upon validation.
  Link TTL: 1 day (filterable: recovery_mode_email_link_ttl).
  URL customisable via filter: recovery_mode_begin_url.
end note

note right of UC5
  <b>Cookie format:</b> base64(recovery_mode|iat|rand|hmac_sha1).
  Valid for WEEK_IN_SECONDS
  (filterable: recovery_mode_cookie_length).
  HMAC signed with AUTH_KEY + AUTH_SALT
  (falls back to auto-generated site options).
  Invalid or expired cookie → clear_cookie() + 403 wp_die().
  Validated before plugins are loaded.
end note

note right of UC7
  Verifies nonce (exit_recovery_mode action).
  Deletes all paused plugin & theme records.
  Clears email rate-limit option.
  Expires recovery mode cookie.
  Also triggered by wp_logout action.
  Redirects to referer or admin dashboard.
end note

@enduml
